originalText: There was a large, coordinated pirate raid on merchant ferries going to Camp Hathor. The Black Eels are promising safety, but I got a bad feeling about all of this...

First the Hathor merchants, then Protectorate ships - the pirates seem stronger than ever. The people are scared, and some folks I talked to have sold their ferries and moved their businesses in-land.

Things are horrible.
If the pirates can raid The Rig, they can raid anything. What's next? Camp Hathor? Junkyard? No one knows, but everyone's scared crapless.
I heard something about that weasel Grover owing some money to Silas and not being able to repay. I figure Black Eels will be coming for him soon, so you better steer clear of him.
I heard some of the captains speak about a place called the "Silent Isle" that's supposedly haunted. Sailors, eh?
You've probably heard by now that Free Drones have taken control of the station above us. Everybody's talking about that.
Scrappers got slaughtered to the last man. But you'd know more about that than me.
Faceless retreated and unblocked the North Tunnel.
Faceless have blockaded the tunnel leading to the North Underrail near Core City. Everyone is wondering why and those who know are not telling.
There was an underground explosion somewhere below the slums. Word on the street is that Scrappers bombed one of the Eels' secret hideouts.
Someone killed Elwood while he was in the Casino. Doesn't surprise me. He owed a lot of money to a number of people.
I heard that Kimi badmouthed her Black Eel patrons. Bad idea.
Newest freak sighting: Two-headed mutants in Old Junkyard. Make of that what you will.
